==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: carousel
<hw>carousel</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧r`⟦osl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>a continuous belt oriented horizontally or
near-horizontally around a central structure, driven in a circular
motion by some mechanism, which carries luggage delivered from the
luggage hold of an airplane to air travelers; -- used at
airports.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> luggage carousel.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>merry-go-round</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> merry-go-round, roundabout, whirligig.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carouser</ent>⟦br⟧
